      • selectQueryDB

        public java.util.Vector<java.util.Vector<java.lang.Object>> selectQueryDB(java.lang.String querySt,
                                                                          int numCols)
        Retrieve selected database values as a list of list of objects.
        Parameters:
        querySt: - Complete select mysql statement.
        numCols: - Number of contiguous columns to be retrieved. It retrieves all columns from the first one until column "numCols"
        Returns:
        Vector of Vector objects. This method can be used when one or more rows are expected to be retrieved Values of one row are stored in vector of objects. All results obtained by each row are stored in one vector of objects. The size of the returned object correspond to the number of rows retrieved from the database. This method must not be used if binary object are expected to be retrieved.

      • loadDB

        public java.util.Vector<java.util.Vector<java.lang.Object>> loadDB(java.lang.String query,
                                                                   java.lang.Object key,
                                                                   int numCols)
        It retrieves a list of binary object from the database. Many rows containing binary objects can be retrieved
        Parameters:
        query: - select mysql statement. Selected table must have only one key of any type.
        key: - A geneic object key. Most of the persistent databases have only one key, which can be either the population's identifier or string value like the population's owner (instructor)
        numCols: - Number of contiguous columns of binary objects to be retrieved. It retrieves all binary objects from the second column until column 'numCols'.
        Returns:
        a list of list of binary object..

      • loadDB

                                                                   java.lang.Object key1,
                                                                   java.lang.Object key2,
                                                                   int numCols)
        It retrieves a list of binary object from the database. Many rows containing binary objects can be retrieved

        key2: - The second generic object key.
